Winter’s bounty, served fresh in every bite of this heart salad! 🍠🍓🍃

Available at @communion_cafe all month! 👩🏻‍🍳 

Winter Harvest Salad

Ingredients:
For the Salad:
	•	1 cup cooked black rice
	•	1 large beetroot, diced
	•	Sweet potato and pumpkin, diced
	•	1 cup mixed greens : Kale + Arugula
	•	1/2 cup strawberries, quartered
	•	1/4 cup toasted walnuts, halved 
	•	2 tbsp toasted pumpkin seeds 
	•	Feta cheese
	•	Olive oil, for roasting
	•	Salt, to taste

For the Vinaigrette:
	•	2 tbsp Dijon mustard
	•	1 tbsp honey
	•	2 tbsp apple cider vinegar
	•	1/4 cup olive oil
	•	Garlic, to taste
	•	Salt and black pepper, to taste

Instructions:
	1.	Roast Veggies: Toss diced beetroot, pumpkin, and sweet potato with olive oil, salt, and pepper. Roast at 400°F (200°C) for 25–30 minutes.
	2.	Prepare Rice: Cook black rice as per instructions and cool.
	3.	Make Vinaigrette: Whisk mustard, honey, orange tang powder, and vinegar. Gradually add olive oil and season with salt, pepper, and garlic.
	4.	Assemble Salad: Combine rice, roasted veggies, mixed greens, strawberries, walnuts, pumpkin seeds, and feta in a bowl. Toss with vinaigrette.
	5.	Serve: Garnish with extra strawberries or walnuts and enjoy!

A vibrant, seasonal salad perfect for winter gatherings!
